text.tspan: Press your pedal for next cue.It is set to the [PgDn] key by default.
For rehearsals, use [a-x] to navigate to a cue.
= Continue this action for a time, then immediately do next action.
= Do these actions immediately, one after the other.
= Play this cue (by tapping on the pedal).
= Improvise by moving your hands around. The velocity of the motion
controls the amplitude of the sound.
= Improvise by moving your hands from the center of your chest
to either side or up and down. This action should be sparse.
= Improvise by cuing sounds above or below your chest
= Copy player 0 in a mechanical manner.
= Copy player 0 in a fluid manner.
= Energy level - indicates the overall energy, as manifested
in characteristics such as loudness, speed and timbre.
R↓= Move your right hand in the position indicated by the arrow.
L↓= Move your left hand in the direction indicated by the arrow.
